The Coral Reef Task Force, created in the Clinton administration, regularly assesses coral health.
With a finished necklace retailing for up to 20,000 dollars (15,000 euros), red corals are among the world's most expensive wildlife commodities.
Caribbean coral species essential to the region's reef ecosystems are at risk of extinction as a result of climate change.
The UN wildlife trade organisation imposed strict limits on the global trade of pink and red coral, severely depleted by commercial exploitation.
But two species of coral last year were listed as "threatened" under the Endangered Species Act.
